    <text>
        <body>
            <div xml:id="d.1">
                <head type="title">[387.] Miklós Oláh to Erasmus of Rotterdam (Brussels, 25 July
                    1533)</head>
                <floatingText type="regesta">
                    <body>
                        <p xml:id="reg.p.1"> Quirinus has returned from England, having completed
                            what Erasmus had assigned him to do. Now he is not entrusting a longer
                            letter to him because he has already written and sent everything with
                            Lieven Algoet. He is really looking forward to Erasmus’ return home. He
                            is helping Pieter Montfoort as much as he can to get a position. The
                            Queen is leaving the day after tomorrow to travel around Flanders for
                            2-3 months.</p>
                    </body>
                </floatingText>
                <pb facs="https://www.eleveltar.hu/kereso-portlet/spring/digitalcontent/getcontent/preservica/37DEDE7B-F11E-4C5B-BAC7-7E0AEAC5E441
                    "/>
                <p xml:id="p.1">Nicolaus Olaus thesaurarius Albensis etc. Erasmo Roterodamo.</p>
                <p xml:id="p.2"><persName>Quirinus</persName><note xml:id="note.1">Quirinus Hagius
                        of The Hague.</note> tuus hoc triduo ex <placeName>Anglia</placeName> ad me
                    rediit confectis istic, ut mihi dixit, rebus tuis omnibus. Longiorem epistolam
                    ad te per eum non dedi. Nam de omnibus antea te per
                        <persName>Levinum</persName><note xml:id="note.2">Lieven Algoet.</note> tum
                    litteris, tum nuntiis feci certiorem.<note xml:id="note.3">See Ep.
                            379.<ref>olahus.tei.15330621_1</ref></note> Sum in exspectatione, ut
                    redeas. Quod felix faustumque sit.</p>
                <p xml:id="p.3"><persName>Petri a Montfort</persName><note xml:id="note.4">See Ep.
                            371.<ref>olahus.tei.15330601_1</ref></note> negotium, quantum in me est,
                    nunc ago, in commendatura<note xml:id="note.5">The office of commander of St.
                        John in Utrecht.</note> consultius et quietius videtur, ut cum altero, qui
                    in absentia sua curavit in successorem viventis commendatoris se eligi,
                    concordaret. De praepositura Harlemmensi<note xml:id="note.6">The Provostry of
                        Haarlem.</note> nunc res agitur, de qua et aliis sacerdotiis nescio quas, ut
                    vocant, rotulas caesar constituit, ut vacaturae quibusdam designatis personis
                    conferrentur. Quod nisi obstiterit, spes est, ut hic <choice>
                        <orig>ο πολυσαρχος</orig>
                        <supplied>ὁ πολύσαρκος</supplied>
                    </choice> αμφοτερω ημων ο φιλτατος<note xml:id="note.7">‘the fat man whom we
                        both love’. Beside Oláh and Erasmus, Jespersen also called Montfoort a fat
                        man, see <hi rend="smallcap">Allen</hi> 1941, 277.</note> voto suo potiatur.
                        <persName>Regina</persName> perendie ad <placeName>Flandriam</placeName>
                    perlustrandam proficiscitur, ubi credo eam haesuram duobus aut tribus mensibus.
                    Quo si reverti te contigeret, praemitte <persName>Levinum</persName>. Vale.</p>
                <p xml:id="p.4"><placeName>Bruxellae</placeName> 25. Iulii <choice>
                        <orig>1531</orig>
                        <supplied>1533</supplied>
                    </choice>.<note xml:id="note.8">According Allen’s edition: “The date given in
                        the MS is shown to be wrong by the contents. Quirinus Hagius was not in
                        England in 1531, but did go there in 1533, in which year Livinus Algoet and
                        Peter Montfoert both went on missions to Erasmus ad Freiburg. The position
                        of the letter in the MS also indicates 1533 as the correct date”, see <hi
                            rend="smallcap">Allen</hi> 1941, 276–277.</note></p>
            </div>
        </body>
